>
	<h2>Roadmap for 2024</h2>
	<p>
		This roadmap highlights the projects, tools, and technologies I'm prioritising for the next year. It reflects my commitment to learning, creating, and improving, while building impactful tools and engaging with open-source communities.
	</p>

	<h3>Immediate Focus (1–3 Months)</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Linkarooie Improvements</strong>: 
			<ul>
				<li>Fix OG image rendering issues and optimise the font setup.</li>
				<li>Transition signups to email validation, removing the invite code system.</li>
				<li>Explore using Kamal for streamlined deployment processes.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li><strong>Astro Blog Enhancements</strong>: 
			<ul>
				<li>Launch a tech-focused quiz system with questions tied to my projects and learnings.</li>
				<li>Improve site performance and design iteratively.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li><strong>Exploring Bun and TypeScript</strong>: Experiment with Bun for server-side development and refine my TypeScript skills with practical projects.</li>
		<li><strong>Bluesky and AT Proto</strong>: Build tools leveraging the Bsky SDK, exploring integrations with decentralised social media.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Mid-Term Goals (3–6 Months)</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>RetroRides</strong>: 
			<ul>
				<li>Finalise the classic car auction scraper pipeline with normalisation in SQLite.</li>
				<li>Develop a lightweight, user-friendly UI for data browsing and export.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li><strong>Terraform and AWS</strong>: 
			<ul>
				<li>Deepen expertise in Docker and ECS deployments with Terraform.</li>
				<li>Expand my Terraform templates for production-grade reliability.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li><strong>LLM Tools</strong>: Create utility tools integrating OpenAI, Anthropic Claude, and Grok to explore practical applications of AI for summarisation, classification, and more.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Long-Term Exploration and Learning (6–12 Months)</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Cloudflare Workers</strong>: Experiment with serverless edge computing and potential integrations with FastAPI and other projects.</li>
		<li><strong>FastAPI and UV</strong>: Build projects using FastAPI for API development and UV for faster workflows.</li>
		<li><strong>Event-Driven Architectures</strong>: Dive into Kafka and RabbitMQ for scalable processing and messaging systems.</li>
		<li><strong>Database Optimisation</strong>: Refine skills in SQLite and PostgreSQL, focusing on performance tuning and scalability.</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Core Principles Driving This Roadmap</h3>
	<p>
		My work is grounded in the following goals:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>**Continuous Improvement**: Sharpening skills with TypeScript, Bun, Terraform, and more.</li>
		<li>**Impactful Solutions**: Prioritising high-value features like Linkarooie improvements and RetroRides development.</li>
		<li>**Open-Source Contributions**: Sharing knowledge through tools, projects, and blog updates.</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		Follow along as I share progress, insights, and milestones. Suggestions, feedback, and collaboration ideas are always welcome!
	</p>
